The National Park Service is celebrating its 99th birthday on Tuesday, August 25, and in celebration, entrance to the following national park units in New York will be free:

* Eleanor Roosevelt National Historic Site

* Home of Franklin D. Roosevelt National Historic Site

* Martin Van Buren National Historic Site

* Sagamore Hill National Historic Site

* Saratoga National Historical Park

* Vanderbilt Mansion National Historic Site

This isn't limited to New York. National parks across the US will be free to enter on August 25 ([here is a complete list of all national parks that usually charge an entrance fee, but will be free](https://www.reddit.com/r/NationalPark/comments/3fiyt0/free_entrance_to_all_national_parks_on_august_25/)).